      • setStrategy

        public void setStrategy(Solution.Strategy strategy)
        Description copied from interface: BuilderIndexProvider
        Sets the iteration strategy parameter to build the index provider. The strategy determines in which order the reagents are given to the reaction rule. An ordered strategy will always give the same order of iteration and lead to the same execution result. A random strategy will allow indeterminism and possibly different results between two executions.
        Specified by:
        setStrategy in interface BuilderIndexProvider
        Parameters:
        strategy - The iteration's order/strategy.
        See Also:
        Solution.Strategy

      • build

        public void build()
           throws ChemicalException
        Proceeds to the building of the index provider. This functions first checks if all the parameters are instantiated, otherwise a ChemicalException explaining the issue is thrown.
        The only operation in this function is then to create a SubIndexProviderSolution builder to build the root SubIndexProviderSolution (see IndexProvider structure). If any error occurs during the building of the SubIndexProviderSolution, the error is directly reported. At the end, the product is declared as complete (_complete is set to true).
        Note: the implementation used to build the IndexProvider is the standard implementation.
        Throws:
        ChemicalException
        See Also:
        IndexProvider, SubIndexProviderSolution, BuilderSubIndexProviderSolution
